    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/arne_glimcher_558104",
        "quote": "When Nixon opened the door to China in the early 1970s, Chinese artists got their first view of the West. Suddenly five centuries of Western art lay before them as a stylistic smorgasbord. Chinese artists could reinterpret it out of admiration or try to replace it. They choose the former.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Arne Glimcher",
            "url": "/quotes/arne_glimcher_558104"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Door",
                "url": "/topics/door"
            },
            {
                "name": "Before",
                "url": "/topics/before"
            },
            {
                "name": "Nixon",
                "url": "/topics/nixon"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/arne_glimcher_558105",
        "quote": "The conceptual artist Ai WeiWei illustrates the schizoid society that rapid change has produced - sometimes by reassembling Ming-style furniture into absurd and useless arrangements, or by carefully painting and antiquing a Coca-Cola logo on an ancient Chinese pot.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Arne Glimcher",
            "url": "/quotes/arne_glimcher_558105"
        },
        "topics": [
