    {
        "url": "/quotes/arne_glimcher_558107",
        "quote": "As a result of World War II, European artists migrated to America, enlarging the scene and diminishing Paris as the center. America was beginning its dominance of the art world with the emergence of the Abstract Expressionists.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Arne Glimcher",
            "url": "/quotes/arne_glimcher_558107"
